<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1901-09-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1901-09-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="102" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d102">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Marroquin</persName>
                                to President <persName type="to">Roosevelt</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Bogotá</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1901-09-23"><hi rend="italic">September 23,
                                    1901</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>May it please your excellency to accept the expressions of condolence of
                            the Colombian Government and people for the demise of the illustrious
                            President McKinley.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">José Manuel Marroquin</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">President of Colombia.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>